---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import KernelPlayground from '../components/KernelPlayground.astro';

const title = 'Playground — Drive the Governance Kernel Live';
const description =
  'Edit a WorldManifest and watch the real ai2rules kernel decide ALLOW / ASK / DENY / ABSENT — compiled to WebAssembly and running entirely in your browser.';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title={title} description={description} />
    <style>
      main {
        width: 1080px;
        max-width: calc(100% - 2em);
      }
      .intro { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
      .intro h1 { font-size: 2rem; margin: 0 0 0.5rem; line-height: 1.1; }
      .intro p { color: var(--gray, #8a97ad); margin: 0; }
      .note {
        margin-top: 1.25rem;
        font-size: 0.85rem;
        color: var(--gray, #8a97ad);
        border-left: 3px solid var(--accent, #5b9bff);
        padding-left: 0.8rem;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>
      <div class="intro">
        <h1>Drive the governance kernel, live</h1>
        <p>
          This isn't a mock-up. Flip the context, toggle which tools exist, or
          pick a preset — and watch tools rearrange between <strong>Allowed</strong>,
          <strong>Ask</strong>, <strong>Denied</strong>, and <strong>Absent</strong>.
          Every verdict is computed by the <strong>real compiler and kernel</strong>
          — the same Rust code the harness uses — compiled to WebAssembly and run
          in your browser.
        </p>
      </div>

      <KernelPlayground />

      <p class="note">
        Try it: switch to <code>Tainted</code> and watch the network / MCP / memory
        tools jump to <code>DENIED</code> — the monotonic taint floor. Untoggle a
        tool and it becomes <code>ABSENT</code>: it stops existing in this world,
        rather than being denied. This is an early bridge build (debug WASM); the
        polished visualization suite is on the way.
      </p>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>
